â­ 1ï½œIntroduction

LLMs operate through complex high-dimensional vector transformations that are not directly observable. Traditional â€œBlack-Boxâ€ and â€œWhite-Boxâ€ explanations are insufficient for describing the emergent semantic structures that occur during inference.

Grey-Box V3 offers a conceptual visualization model that maps LLM reasoning into seven interpretable layers:

Node

Attention

Flow

Weight

Velocity

Intervention

Semantic Field (V3 æ–°å¢)

This framework helps researchers, engineers, and designers understand and debug LLM behavior.

